    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 packs of ramen noodles</li>
            <li>4 cups chicken or vegetable broth</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon miso paste</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 cup sliced shiitake mushrooms</li>
            <li>1 cup baby spinach</li>
            <li>4 soft-boiled eggs, halved</li>
            <li>4 green onions, sliced</li>
            <li>Nori (seaweed) sheets, for garnish</li>
            <li>Sesame seeds, for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Ramen</li>
            <li>Noodles</li>
            <li>Soup</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Comfort Food</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Cook the ramen noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, heat the broth over medium heat. Add soy sauce, miso paste, sesame oil, grated ginger, and minced garlic. Stir until the miso paste is dissolved.</li>
            <li>Add sliced shiitake mushrooms to the broth and simmer for 5 minutes until they are tender.</li>
            <li>Divide the cooked ramen noodles among serving bowls. Ladle the hot broth and mushrooms over the noodles.</li>
            <li>Top each bowl with baby spinach, soft-boiled eggs, sliced green onions, nori sheets, and sesame seeds.</li>
            <li>Serve the Ramen hot and enjoy this comforting and flavorful dish!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

